targetSentence: Nevertheless, several recent papers provide empirical evidence that LLMs fail to capture important aspects of linguistic meaning. [SEP] Focusing on universal quantification, we provide a theoretical foundation for these empirical findings by proving that [MASK] cannot learn certain fundamental semantic properties including semantic entailment and consistency as they are defined in formal semantics. [SEP] More generally, we show that LLMs are unable to learn concepts beyond the first level of the Borel Hierarchy, which imposes severe limits on the ability of LMs, both large and small, to capture many aspects of linguistic meaning.
